function x = ifft2c(x,varargin)%IFFT2C Centered inverse discrete Fourier transform.%	IFFT2C(X) is the centered inverse discrete Fourier transform of X.%%	IFFT2C(X,N) is the N-point inverse transform.% %	IFFT2C(X,[],DIM) or IFFTC(X,N,DIM) is the inverse discrete Fourier%	transform of X across the dimension DIM.%%	See also FFTC, IFFT, FFT, FFT2, IFFT2, FFTN, IFFTN, FFTSHIFT.%	v1.0, 6/25/01, Michael Butterfield, <gte881s@prism.gatech.edu>%	v1.1, 6/26/01, Erik Zeek, <zeekec@mad.scientist.com>%		Updated help.  Changed to VARARGIN implementation.%%	$Revision: 1.3 $ $Date: 2002/04/18 22:05:29 $%%	$Log: ifftc.m,v $%	Revision 1.3  2002/04/18 22:05:29  zeekec%	Reused the input as the output.%	%	Revision 1.2  2001/07/10 01:10:00  zeekec%	Library cleanup.  Added, deleted, and moved files.%	%x = ifftshift(ifft2(fftshift(x),varargin{:}));